{
  "texts": [
    "Bias in language professionalism states that male candidates are considered more \"professional\" than females.",
    "For instance, Trix and Psenka (2003) revealed the gender schema where women are seen as less capable and less professional than men.",
    "Khan et al. (2021) also observed more mentions of personal life in letters for female candidates.",
    "Gender biases in this dimension will lead to biased information on candidates' professionalism, therefore resulting in unfair hiring evaluation.",
    "Bias in language excellency states that male candidates are described using more \"excellent\" language than female candidates in professional documents (Trix and Psenka, 2003; Madera et al., 2009 Madera et al.,, 2019))."
  ]
}